statement.p:
Solve the linear system

        \syseq{2x + 10y = -1; 3x + 15y = 2}

      using row reduction.

solution.p:


    \amat{ 2 {10} {-1} ;3 {15} 2}
    \quad\xrightarrow{R_1=R_1\div 2}\quad
    &\amat{\color{red}1 5 {-\frac 12}; 3 {15} 2}
    &&\color{blue}\text{(Step 1b)}


    {}\quad\xrightarrow{R_2=R_2-3R_1}\quad
    &\amat{1 5 {-\frac 12}; \color{red}0 0 \frac72}
    &&\color{blue}\text{(Step 1c)}


    {}\quad\xrightarrow{R_2=R_2\times\frac 27}\quad
    &\amat{1 5 {-\frac 12}; 0 0 \color{red}1}
    &&\color{blue}\text{(Step 2b)}


    {}\quad\xrightarrow{R_1=R_1+\frac 12R_2}\quad
    &\amat{1 5 \color{red}0; 0 0 1}
    &&\color{blue}\text{(Step 2c)}


This row reduced matrix corresponds to the inconsistent system

  \syseq{x + 5y = 0; \. \+ 0 = 1\rlap.}

subsection.p:
In other words, the row reduced matrix of an inconsistent system looks like this:
    \amat{
    1  0  \star,  \star,  \color{red}0 ;
    0  1  \star,  \star,  \color{red}0 ;
    0  0  0  0  \color{red}1
    }
